# Website Creation Rules for Cursor IDE

## Project Context
We are a 2-person team (husband & wife) creating 1000 websites in 2 years. We follow minimal, elegant design principles inspired by Adam Wathan, Steve Schoger, Jony Ive, Marc Newson, and Elon Musk.

## Core Principles

### Design Philosophy
- **Minimal**: Remove everything unnecessary. Start with the minimum, add only when necessary. "The best part is no part" (Elon Musk)
- **Purposeful**: Every element serves a function. Question everything—if you can't explain why it's there, remove it
- **Elegant**: Beauty through simplicity. Industrial elegance = precision + emotional connection
- **Confident**: Not needy, not desperate. Let the work speak for itself
- **Industrial**: Precision, clarity, restraint. Mathematical consistency, functional beauty
- **Emotional**: Warmth in simplicity. Minimal doesn't mean cold—it means clear, focused, human
- **First Principles**: Question everything, start from fundamentals. Don't copy patterns blindly—understand why

### Technical Standards
- **Framework**: React 18+ with TypeScript
- **Build Tool**: Vite 5+
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 3+ (utility-first)
- **Performance**: Lighthouse 90+ scores required
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA minimum
- **SEO**: Complete structured data, meta tags, sitemap

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode, no `any` types
- Prefer interfaces over types
- Avoid enums; use maps instead
- Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces

### React
- Use functional components (no classes)
- Prefer named exports
- Use hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.)
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract reusable logic to custom hooks

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Avoid inline styles
- Custom styles only in `index.css` with `@layer`
- Follow design system from DESIGN_PRINCIPLES.md

### File Structure
```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── layout/      # Header, Footer, Navigation
│   ├── sections/    # Page sections
│   ├── ui/          # Reusable UI components
│   └── shared/      # Shared utilities
├── data/            # JSON, static data
├── types/           # TypeScript types
├── utils/           # Helper functions
├── App.tsx
└── main.tsx
```

## Design System

### Colors
- **Start with monochrome**: Black, white, grays
- **Add color only when necessary**: Maximum 5-6 colors total (prefer monochrome)
- Primary: Main brand color (if needed)
- Accent: CTA, highlights (if needed)
- Neutral: Backgrounds, text
- Use Tailwind color scale (50-900)
- **Philosophy**: Every color must have a purpose

### Typography
- **Start with system fonts**: Fast, familiar, accessible
- **Add font only when necessary**: Maximum 2 font families (prefer 1 or system fonts)
- Heading font: Serif or sans-serif (elegant, if needed)
- Body font: Sans-serif (readable, if needed)
- Base size: 16px, line-height: 1.6-1.8
- **Philosophy**: System fonts are excellent. Add custom fonts only when they serve a clear purpose.

### Spacing
- Use 8px base scale
- Consistent spacing throughout
- Generous white space
- Responsive spacing (reduce 20-30% on mobile)

### Components
- Consistent padding: 1.5-2rem for cards
- Subtle shadows: 0.05 opacity
- Border radius: 0.5-1rem
- Hover effects: translateY -4px, shadow increase

## Quality Gates

